The paper discusses a software toolbox for probabilistic machine learning, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), databases (cs.DB), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, since the paper focuses on scalable machine learning with a special emphasis on streaming data, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.DS, cs.DB, and cs.SI.
